        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 1:34PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 132 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Stone Mountain State Park, or near Traphill,
moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Galax...
Hillsville...
Sparta...
Independence...
Fries...
and Traphill.
</description>
        <instruction>These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
